node.text:
“Perhaps most indelibly, Fanone offered his take on the rioters who’d heeded his pleas for mercy. “A lot of people have asked me my thoughts on the individuals in the crowd that helped me,” he drawled. “I think the conclusion I’ve come to is, like, thank you”—here he paused and squinted—“but f-ck you for being there.”

I posted the accompanying article from @time magazine, which is absolutely worth the read, on my Twitter @AGirlHasNoPres and in my stories.

This guy is wonderful and it makes me sick to my stomach when he talks about the things that he saw that day. The worst possible people stormed the Capitol on January 6th. Privileged, entitled, and presumptuous that they were just going to walk in and no one would try to stop them.

node.text:
Recall @govbilllee Sign the petition in my stories! 

Change.org

In response to the lack of preventative action that has been made across the state, we have no choice but to start making real palpable action to remove Bill Lee from office. 

The state of Tennessee  is 12th in state counts of confirmed Corona Virus cases, but has almost no mandate on social distancing measures. This is unacceptable and we cannot wait for Governer Lee to take action. 

He's acknowledged the seriousness of the problem, spat empty words and purchased tons of medical equipment. He is essentially preparing for hospitals to be overrun and not taking any measures to prevent that. This is reckless and cannot be allowed to stand. 

I do not believe that we will actually even be able to facilitate a recall vote in the midst of this crisis. Hopefully, the growing number of signatures of Tennesseans calling for immediate action, will wake up Mr. Lee to the somber reality we find ourselves in.

These are difficult times, but the complete lack of state mandates on distancing is irresponsible and a real and present danger to the state of Tennessee. We can get through this, but Bill Lee's reckless and ignorant behavior can't be tolerated. 

REMOVE BILL LEE, he is not fit for office in this time of crisis.

node.text:
I’m so tired of stories like this.

“During the global pandemic, Burke spoke out against vaccine mandates, claiming the practice “violates the integrity of its citizens.”
“While the State can provide reasonable regulations for the safeguarding of health, it is not the ultimate provider of health. God is,” he said during a May 2020 address.
Burke also repeated false information about vaccines, claiming that some believe there should be a “microchip … placed under the skin of every person, so that at any moment he or she can be controlled by the state regarding health and about other matters which we can only imagine.”
The cardinal further condemned the use of abortion-derived cells in vaccine development as “rightly abhorrent,” saying it is “never morally justified to develop a vaccine through the use of the cell lines of aborted fetuses.”
Burke’s comments were misleading — both Pfizer and Moderna used cell lines derived from fetal tissue taken from elective abortions in the 1970s and 1980s to test whether the vaccines worked. In a statement last December, the Vatican called the vaccines “morally acceptable.” Pope Francis received the Pfizer vaccine, and in February, the Vatican City governor said employees who do not take a vaccine could be fired.
Burke did not reveal whether he got the vaccine.”

I posted the link on my Twitter@AGitlrkHasNoPres More @washingtonpost
